# ============================================================================
# dag_workflow.dag — DAGMan workflow: run simulations, then collect results
# ============================================================================
# This DAGMan file chains two jobs:
#   1. BATCH — 50 Monte Carlo simulations (run in parallel)
#   2. COLLECT — combines all results into one summary file
#
# DAGMan ensures COLLECT only runs after ALL 50 BATCH jobs finish.
#
# Submit with:
#   condor_submit_dag must/dag_workflow.dag
#
# Monitor with:
#   condor_q                          # see running jobs
#   cat must/dag_workflow.dag.dagman.out  # DAGMan log
#
# The DAG creates its own log files alongside this file:
#   must/dag_workflow.dag.dagman.out
#   must/dag_workflow.dag.dagman.log
#   must/dag_workflow.dag.lib.out
# ============================================================================

# Step 1: Run 50 Monte Carlo simulations (each with a different seed)
JOB  BATCH    must/run_batch.sub

# Step 2: Collect and summarize all simulation results
JOB  COLLECT  must/collect_results.sub

# Dependency: COLLECT waits for all BATCH jobs to finish
PARENT BATCH CHILD COLLECT
